<p>Ivory Coast held a presidential vote on Saturday as incumbent Alassane Ouattara, 83, ran for a fourth term while crediting nearly 15 years of economic growth and relative stability and suggesting it may be his final campaign . The election takes place after key opposition figures were barred from standing, prompting critics to allege the contest lacks fairness and has been manipulated . Voting proceeded in major cities including Abidjan amid a tense atmosphere and local reports of eager queues at some polling stations .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/LZAVOogh0bQMOzlG05rT2bXCp6AfAv5vee4wUt9pv1Lwj0oEKPUJNGF_XkYSUq3YVrtYzCxJsjkdoV9v_cjqFFwngVl1TgbvYyMcTvBBWMBQO-m5bsrIDpB6EO8RVtD2do1rxyEuyOM3SVboUBWIbK7B7PE2sPOxvb-y6s4L3LEpH7UjdCzYE1nh3x4' alt='President Alassane Ouattara waving at supporters at his final rally in Abidjan before the election.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Term-limit context: Ivory Coast&#x27;s constitution limits presidents to two terms, yet Ouattara is seeking a fourth term, a legal and political fault line cited by critics .</li><li>Who’s on ballot: Five candidates were listed on the ballot, with Ouattara among them, after several high-profile rivals were excluded from running .</li><li>Campaign scenes: At a final rally in Abidjan just before voting, Ouattara greeted supporters in person, an image captured days before the election .</li><li>Security incidents: Authorities arrested roughly 700 people during protests in the lead-up to voting, according to local reporting on unrest tied to the campaign .</li><li>Voter energy: Journalists reported voters arriving as early as 6 a.m. in neighborhoods such as Treichville, reflecting visible turnout enthusiasm in parts of Abidjan .</li></ul><blockquote>People look very eager to cast their ballot - Justice Baidoo</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Alassane Ouattara: He credits nearly 15 years of economic growth and relative stability and has described this campaign as likely his final run. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Ivory-Coast-votes-with-Ouattaras-legacy-age-in-focus'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>Opposition critics: They argue main challengers were excluded from the ballot and say the vote has been manipulated, undermining its credibility. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/25/world/africa/ivory-coast-election.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li><li>Local voters/journalists: Reporters on the ground described eager turnout in neighborhoods like Treichville, with some voters arriving before dawn. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251025-people-look-very-eager-to-cast-their-ballot-after-a-tumultous-build-up-to-the-election'>France 24</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Ivory-Coast-votes-with-Ouattaras-legacy-age-in-focus'>Ivory Coast votes with Ouattara&#x27;s legacy, age in focus</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/25/world/africa/ivory-coast-election.html'>Presidents Are Limited to Two Terms. He’s Running for His Fourth.</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/25/ivory-coast-presidential-election-whos-standing-and-whats-at-stake'>Ivory Coast presidential election: Who’s standing and what’s at stake?</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/polls-open-ivory-coast-incumbent-ouattara-seeks-fourth-126856825'>Polls open in Ivory Coast as incumbent Ouattara seeks a fourth term</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251025-people-look-very-eager-to-cast-their-ballot-after-a-tumultous-build-up-to-the-election'>&#x27;People look very eager to cast their ballot&#x27; after a tumultous build-up to the election</a> - france24.com</li></ul>